claim.claim-text:
An exhaust gas purification device of an internal combustion engine, comprising:
a filter that is provided in an exhaust passage of the internal combustion engine and configured to collect particulate matter in an exhaust gas;
urea water spraying means that is provided in the exhaust passage downstream of the filter and configured to spray urea water into the exhaust gas;
a selective reduction catalyst that is provided in the exhaust passage downstream of the urea water spraying means and configured to reduce and purify a nitrogen compound in the exhaust gas by using ammonia produced from the urea water;
electrostatic capacity detecting means configured to detect an electrostatic capacity of the filter;
accumulation amount calculating means configured to calculate an amount of accumulated particulate matter collected by the filter, based on the detected electrostatic capacity;
consumption amount estimating means configured to estimate an amount of nitrogen dioxide consumed by the particulate matter that has accumulated in the filter, based on the calculated amount of accumulated particulate matter; and
controlling means configured to control a combustion state of the internal combustion engine such that a ratio of carbon monoxide to nitrogen dioxide in the exhaust gas flowing into the selective reduction catalyst approaches 1 to 1, based on the estimated amount of consumed nitrogen dioxide.
